## Strict typing (non-negotiable)
- All functions have explicit parameter and return types
- Use `py.typed` marker in packages for PEP 561
- Run pyright/mypy in strict mode

## Pydantic models, not dicts
- Never use `dict` as input or output of functions
- Use Pydantic `BaseModel` for structured data
- Avoids syntax errors (e.g. missing `)`) and enables validation
